<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1440,1698,1754]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,339,1698,1722]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named for Robin O. S. Clarke (Hotel Flora and Fauna, Buena Vista, 
<collectingCountry box="[1173,1260,1698,1722]" name="Bolivia" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
) in recognition of his many taxonomic contributions to the knowledge of New World 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1040,1220,1730,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cerambycidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1441,1794,1914]" lastBlockId="5.[192,1441,194,666]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,316,1794,1818]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Wappes, 2017" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2017" box="[330,557,1794,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clarkei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[330,557,1794,1818]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Coleoxestia clarkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[564,658,1794,1817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1884)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[817,1168,1794,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis box="[817,997,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C. sanguinipes</emphasis>
(Bates, 1884)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs as follows: distance between upper eye lobes in male 1.50 times width of one lobe; distance between upper eye lobes in female 1.45 times width of one lobe; antennomeres dark; antennomere IV uniformly enlarged from base to apex at outer side, not enlarged near apex of inner side; sides of prothorax not distinctly plicate; elytra shining, not or slightly vermiculate into network in basal half; tibiae entirely black. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Fragoso, S. A." box="[224,411,226,250]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="327 - 343" refId="ref11927" refString="Fragoso, S. A. 1993. On old and new species of Coleoxestia Aurivillius, 1912 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Cerambycinae). Revista Brasileira de Biologia 53 (3): 327 - 343." type="journal article" year="1993">Fragoso (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, one of the 
<typeStatus box="[556,665,226,250]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[704,886,226,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis box="[704,886,226,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. sanguinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sex not specified, but apparently a female): distance between upper eye lobes 1.9 times width of one lobe; antennomeres reddish after distal area of antennomere III; antennomere IV abruptly enlarged near apex (both sides); sides of prothorax plicate; elytra shining (but not vitreous, distinctly duller than on pronotum) (according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Eya, B. K. &amp; J. A. Chemsak" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref11882" refString="Eya, B. K., and J. A. Chemsak. 2005. Review of the genus Coleoxestia Aurivillius of Mexico &amp; Central America, part I (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae), Les Cahiers Magellanes 44: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2005">Eya and Chemsak (2005)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[281,457,354,377]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis box="[281,457,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. sanguinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has “surface slightly opaque, vermiculate into network with a puncture in center”; “coriaceous in appearance”); tibiae gradually lighter toward apex. It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Eya and Chemsak, 2005" authorityName="Eya and Chemsak" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuratai">
<emphasis box="[1256,1383,386,410]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. kuratai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Eya, B. K. &amp; J. A. Chemsak" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref11882" refString="Eya, B. K., and J. A. Chemsak. 2005. Review of the genus Coleoxestia Aurivillius of Mexico &amp; Central America, part I (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae), Les Cahiers Magellanes 44: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2005">Eya and Chemsak, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the tibiae sulcate laterally, from near base to distal third (not sulcate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eya and Chemsak" authorityYear="2005" box="[225,353,450,474]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuratai">
<emphasis box="[225,353,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. kuratai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennomere IV as above described (as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[906,1089,450,473]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis box="[906,1089,450,473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. sanguinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eya and Chemsak" authorityYear="2005" box="[1186,1313,450,474]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuratai">
<emphasis box="[1186,1313,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. kuratai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). From 
<taxonomicName authority="Eya and Chemsak (2005)" authorityName="Eya and Chemsak" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatepunctata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. striatepunctata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Eya, B. K. &amp; J. A. Chemsak" box="[386,694,481,506]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref11882" refString="Eya, B. K., and J. A. Chemsak. 2005. Review of the genus Coleoxestia Aurivillius of Mexico &amp; Central America, part I (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae), Les Cahiers Magellanes 44: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2005">Eya and Chemsak (2005)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
it differs mainly by the antennomere III shorter and thicker, and the pronotum distinctly less rugose-punctate and not distinctly raised medially on basal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1441,194,666]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName authority="Santos-Silva &amp; Wappes, 2017" authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Wappes" authorityYear="2017" box="[240,470,546,570]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clarkei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[240,470,546,570]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Coleoxestia clarkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[481,578,546,569]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be included in the alternative of couplet “13” from 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, U. R. &amp; M. A. Monne" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 218" refId="ref12095" refString="Martins, U. R., and M. A. Monne. 2005. Tribo Cerambycini, Subtribo Sphallotrichina, p. 1 - 218. In: U. R. Martins (org.). Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Taxonomia. EDUSP, Sao Paulo, v. 5. v + 284 p." type="book chapter" year="2005">Martins and Monné (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. However, as some characters used in this alternative of couplet (dimensions, color, elytral sculpture) are variable in the species, they cannot be used to correctly separate it from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[1252,1433,610,633]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis box="[1252,1433,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. sanguinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Waterhouse, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[192,544,642,666]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">
<emphasis box="[192,297,642,666]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. polita</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Waterhouse, C. O." box="[313,536,642,666]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="485 - 488" refId="ref12204" refString="Waterhouse, C. O. 1880. New Cerambycidae from Ecuador. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History (5) 5: 485 - 488." type="journal article" year="1880">Waterhouse, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins and Monne, 2005" authorityName="Martins and Monne" authorityYear="2005" box="[606,1107,641,666]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Coleoxestia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anthracina">
<emphasis box="[606,777,642,666]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C. anthracina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martins, U. R. &amp; M. A. Monne" box="[784,1107,641,666]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 218" refId="ref12095" refString="Martins, U. R., and M. A. Monne. 2005. Tribo Cerambycini, Subtribo Sphallotrichina, p. 1 - 218. In: U. R. Martins (org.). Cerambycidae Sul-Americanos (Coleoptera). Taxonomia. EDUSP, Sao Paulo, v. 5. v + 284 p." type="book chapter" year="2005">Martins and Monné, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
